      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "tent of revelation",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Germ. ‘Offenbarungszelt’); both in E, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 33:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 11:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 12:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and no fewer than 132 times in P; not elsewhere in Deut., in which indeed the Tabernacle is mentioned only here.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that I may give him a charge",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 3:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Moses is commanded to charge Joshua.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "14–23. Again Joshua’s Commission, with Introduction to Moses’ Song",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The composition is very curious. In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 31:14-15; Deuteronomy 31:23",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 31:14-15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 31:23",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " we have an account of the charge to Joshua, which is in substance not the continuation of the deuteronomic one in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 31:1-8",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 31:1-8",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but parallel to that, and is couched in a phraseology resembling that of E (see notes), to which source it is generally assigned. It is interrupted by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 31:16-22",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 31:16-22",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which have nothing to do with Joshua, but are an address of the Lord to Moses, and without connection with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 31:14-15",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Deuteronomy 31:14-15",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", except that the motive in both cases is the imminent death of Moses. The language, while containing some phrases of E and some deuteronomic formulas, gives to the latter a peculiar turn, and contains besides elements not elsewhere found in the Hex. and speaks of Israel in the masc. sing. in a fashion confined to itself. The passage forms an introduction to the Song in ch. 32. Its source is uncertain.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
